lzh_formatted:
  title: 石房途中
  author: 韓脩
  language: lzh
  text: 巉巖石路倦躋攀。何寺踈鍾遠出山。畏日已升靑嶂表。宿雲猶在翠松閒。
korean:
  title: 석방도중
  author: 한수
  language: kor
  text: |-
    높은 바위 돌길을 더위잡고 오르나니
    어느 절 종소리가 먼 산에서 들리는가
    뜨거운 해 푸른 산 밖을 오르는 것 두려워선지
    밤 샌 구름 그저 푸른 솔 사이에 걸려 있구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_1030&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: On the Path to Stone House
  author: Han Soo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Steep rocky paths exhaust my weary climb.
    From which temple does the distant bell toll beyond the mountains?
    The fierce sun rises above the verdant peaks—
    I fear its heat. Yet lingering night clouds
    still cling to the green pines.
  footnotes:
    - Stone House (石房) likely refers to a temple or hermitage nestled in the mountains
    - The bell's distant sound suggests both the spiritual presence and the speaker's distance from human civilization
